Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama had 29 points, seven rebounds, one assist, three blocks, and three turnovers in 30:12 minutes of play.
The San Antonio Spurs had a 22-point lead at one stage and entered halftime with a 62-41 advantage.
The Houston Rockets trimmed the lead to one in the fourth quarter, but the Spurs recorded a 109-106 win.
Wembanyama scored 15 points in the first half and 14 in the second half, including five points in the final quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Victor Wembanyama compensated for his underwhelming opening night performance against the Dallas Mavericks by delivering a strong performance against the Houston Rockets.
Wembanyama's improved size and strength were evident in his performance, particularly in generating free throw attempts.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Spurs outscored the Rockets 52-42 in the paint and had a 28-21 advantage at the free-throw line.
